# Engram bench-harness environment variables.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in the keys
# you need. The bench CLI auto-loads `.env` before resolving the
# provider, so you don't have to set anything in your shell.
#
# You only need the keys for the providers you actually use:
#   * OpenAI       -- embeddings (always required for real-provider runs)
#                     + chat (when --chat openai)
#   * Anthropic    -- chat only (when --chat anthropic)
#   * Moonshot     -- chat only (when --chat moonshot, for Kimi K2.x direct)
#   * OpenCode     -- chat only (when --chat opencode-zen or --chat opencode-go).
#                     Zen and Go share the same OpenCode account API key;
#                     OPENCODE_API_KEY works for both.
#                     - Zen: Claude, GPT 5.x, Kimi K2.x (pay-as-you-go credits)
#                     - Go:  Kimi K2.x, GLM, DeepSeek, MiniMax, Qwen 3.x
#                            (subscription, open-weight models only)
#   * OpenRouter   -- chat AND embeddings (when --chat openrouter / --embedder openrouter).
#                     One key fronts every frontier model (Claude, GPT, Gemini,
#                     Kimi, DeepSeek, Grok, Qwen) PLUS the strongest open
#                     embedders (qwen3-embedding-8b, gemini-embedding-001,
#                     openai/text-embedding-3-large, bge-m3).
#
# Existing environment variables take precedence over `.env`, so you
# can override per-shell without editing this file.

# OpenAI -- https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# Anthropic -- https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Moonshot / Kimi -- https://platform.moonshot.ai/
# (Optional; only needed if you run with --chat moonshot)
MOONSHOT_API_KEY=ms-...

# OpenCode (Zen + Go) -- https://opencode.ai/
# One key works for both plans. Put it under OPENCODE_API_KEY (preferred),
# or the plan-specific aliases OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY / OPENCODE_GO_API_KEY.
# Whichever is set first (in that order) wins.
OPENCODE_API_KEY=...

# OpenRouter -- https://openrouter.ai/keys
# Frontier chat + paid embeddings catalog under one key. Optional ranking
# headers (HTTP-Referer + X-Title) default to Engram's repo; override via
# OPENROUTER_HTTP_REFERER / OPENROUTER_X_TITLE if you want a custom
# attribution on OpenRouter's public dashboard.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...
# OPENROUTER_HTTP_REFERER=https://github.com/AmeyaBorkar/Engram
# OPENROUTER_X_TITLE=Engram

# LongMemEval suite knobs (optional; defaults are fine).
# LONGMEMEVAL_MAX_QUESTIONS=10   # cap for smoke runs; unset = all 500
# LONGMEMEVAL_K=10               # retrieval top-k
